    <h1>Make any web page accessible!</h1>
    <p>BlindPages unlocks the web for blind and partially-sighted people, in just a few easy steps:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Pick the inaccessible site you want to read. </li>
      <li>Ask our team of volunteers and ace programmers to use BlindPages tools to define an accessible view of the inaccessible page.</li>
      <li>Use BlindPages to get the accessible, screenreader-friendly version of the page online, in your existing browser.</li>
      <li>Or pick up a telephone and <em>hear</em> the page content with easy push-button navigation.</li> 
    </ol>

    <p><a href="more">Click to find out more!</a></p>

    <p>Unannotated pictures, too-clever Javascript, content buried in layers of junk, even some types of Flash applications and Java applets - BlindPages can help with nearly any accessibility problem. There's nothing to download or install - BlindPages runs in your existing browser, or on any type of phone (fixed-line, mobile, or VOIP).</p>

    <p>Don't want to wait for a volunteer? Unlock pages yourself if you have programming skills, or get a sighted friend to help!</p>

    <p>Best of all, BlindPages doesn't require any changes by the owner of the page you want to use. Get the content you want, whether or not the page was designed to be accessible!</p>

